<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-521-388  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 521 388.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  August 14 1989 v6 n32 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>COS trims staff 40%, refines focus. (Corporation for Open SystemsInternational)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Runnoe, Gail.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Corporation for Open Systems International (COS) is planningto lay off 40 percent of its employees because revenue from OpenSystems Interconnection (OSI) conformance testing products andservices fell below projections.andP;  COS reports membership hasremained constant, but revenues only increased 20 percent.andP;  Thecompany plans to focus on five priority efforts: promotion andexpansion of the COS Mark Program, promotion of interoperabilitytesting, coordination of efforts with other internationalstandards groups, sponsorship of outside OSI testing andincreasing COS membership.andP;  User reaction to COS's downsizing andrefocus is mostly favorable.andP;  COS currently has 60 members, ofwhich 25 percent are user companies.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Corporation for Open Systems InternationalLayoffManagementRevenueOSI StandardBusiness Planning.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>